A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Education – Artificial Intelligence – Guidelines, Professional Development, and
3 Task Force
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the State Department of Education, in consultation with the
5 State Board of Education, and the Task Force on Artificial Intelligence in K–12
6 Education, to develop or update certain guidance and strategies on artificial
7 intelligence for county boards of education; requiring the State Department of
8 Education, in consultation with the Department of Information Technology, to
9 develop and update annually a list of approved artificial intelligence tools; requiring
10 each county board to designate an employee to facilitate the use of artificial
11 intelligence in the local school system and to conduct an annual inventory of systems
12 that employ artificial intelligence; requiring the Career and Technical Education
13 Committee to ensure that artificial intelligence literacy is a component of workforce
14 preparation; requiring the State Department of Education, in consultation with
15 certain entities, to develop and administer a certain artificial intelligence needs
16 assessment; requiring the State Department of Education to promote training and
17 workforce development in artificial intelligence; establishing the Task Force on
18 Artificial Intelligence in K–12 Education; and generally relating to artificial
19 intelligence in primary and secondary education.
