16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
17 (a) There is a Task Force on Artificial Intelligence in K–12 Education.
18 (b) The Task Force consists of the following members:
19 (1) the State Superintendent, or the State Superintendent’s designee;
20 (2) the Executive Director of the Maryland Association of Boards of
21 Education, or the Executive Director’s designee;
22 (3) the President of the Maryland State Education Association, or the
23 President’s designee;
24 (4) the President of the Maryland Association of School Personnel
25 Administrators, or the President’s designee;
26 (5) the Executive Director of the Public School Superintendents’
27 Association of Maryland, or the Executive Director’s designee;
28 (6) a teacher, student, or parent from each local school system, appointed
29 by the county superintendent; and

