1 (7) the employees designated by the county boards under § 7–2202(c) of the
2 Education Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act.
3 (c) It is the intent of the General Assembly that the teachers appointed or
4 designated to the Task Force shall represent diverse subject areas.
5 (d) The State Superintendent of Schools shall designate the chair of the Task
6 Force from the Department and may establish subcommittees of the Task Force.
7 (e) The Department:
8 (1) shall provide staff for the Task Force; and
9 (2) may partner or contract with an organization to support the Task Force.
10 (f) A member of the Task Force:
11 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Task Force; but
12 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
13 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
14 (g) The Task Force shall:
15 (1) study the uses of artificial intelligence in each local school system,
16 including a review of innovation by industry and philanthropic support of schools in the
17 use of artificial intelligence; and
18 (2) make findings and recommendations regarding:
19 (i) the development or update of guidance and best practices for
20 county boards under § 7–2202 of the Education Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act;
21 (ii) the implementation of best practices for relevant professional
22 development;
23 (iii) the development and administration of the statewide artificial
24 intelligence needs assessment; and
25 (iv) the adoption of policies and procedures regarding the
26 development, procurement, implementation, utilization, and ongoing assessment of
27 systems that employ artificial intelligence by a county board.
28 (h) The Task Force shall coordinate with the Department, the CTE Committee,
29 and the CTE Skills Standards Advisory Committee to provide recommendations for

